description: From Middle English mischeosen, mischesen, equivalent to mis- +‎ choose.

verbs.description: mischoose (third-person singular simple present mischooses, present participle mischoosing, simple past mischose, past participle mischosen)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive) To choose incorrectly or badly; to make a wrong choice.
examples: Up to a certain point he was a free agent , he could choose his path ; he mischose it , and he was in the toils of necessity
